3. We then iterate through the `wordIndexes` array to find the minimum index of the occurrence of the search word.
4. The solution returns the index of the first occurrence of the search word or -1 if the word doesn't appear in the sentence.

Note: The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the sentence once. The space complexity is O(n) because we store n indices in the `wordIndexes` array. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few comparisons and array accesses.

